<dl id="n12004f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12004f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12004f"> 4(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> smooth from kneeprayer</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Dans les C&ocirc;tes-du-Nord aussi, l&apos;un des piliers du dolmen de Coadou est totalement lisse; on explique le poli de sa surface par le fait que saint Briac, saint Iltut et saint Martin s&apos;y donnaient rendez-vous pour prier en commun. <br><font color="green">[Also, in the C&ocirc;tes-du-Nord, one of the pillars of the Coadou dolmen is <mark>completely smooth</mark>. The explanation given for the smoothness of its surface is that Saint Briac, Saint Iltut and Saint Martin used to meet there to pray together.]</font> <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 9</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: ?244.36 77.173 </mm> </dd></dl>
